It's clear the founders intent was that citizens only should count in the US census, because congressional representation is based on that head count and illegal aliens do not fall under that purview. They do not get the representation that US citizens get yet they are still counted toward the number of congressional seats.

It's a blatant contradiction of the reason for the head count in the first place. The founders also carved out an exemption for "Indians Not Taxed"  specifically identifying those living under tribal sovereignty, which was exactly to designate them as non-citizens. 

Then in 1924 the Indian Citizenship Act granted U.S. citizenship to all Native Americans born in the United States, which made the original wording of the constitution moot. But wait a moment, that's exactly because the Indian Citizenship Act identified all native Americans as US citizens and therefore allowed for them to be included in the census count. 

That's the act which clarified the fact that the census count should include only citizens. So why the fuck are people ignoring this and counting illegal aliens still? It must stop. When it stops ALL of this madness stops. No more riots, no more anti ICE nonsense, no more injunctions, that all goes away because they would no longer be anything to gain politically from embracing illegal aliens.
